						<summary>

						<p>This inscription registers an endowment of land after purchase for feeding a <hi rend="italic">Vēda-Brāhmaṇa</hi> every midday in the temple at Tiruviśalūr by <hi rend="bold">Pirāntakaṉ Iruṅgōḷaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śiṟiyavēḷār of Koḍumbāḷūr</hi>, who was a general of king <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka II Sundara-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

